1
00:00:00,224 --> 00:00:01,459
<i>Previously on Reign...</i>

2
00:00:01,460 --> 00:00:03,360
You killed someone in the woods

3
00:00:03,376 --> 00:00:06,178
<i>when the pagans forced
you to choose a sacrifice.</i>

4
00:00:06,246 --> 00:00:07,879
I murdered a man who was
about to kill another.

5
00:00:07,947 --> 00:00:10,115
And to this day I wonder:
did he have a family?

6
00:00:10,183 --> 00:00:11,617
I have very powerful uncles.

7
00:00:11,684 --> 00:00:12,984
What, the Duke of Guise?

8
00:00:13,019 --> 00:00:14,353
Do you have any idea what you've done?

9
00:00:14,420 --> 00:00:16,288
You just let the devil into our home.

10
00:00:18,391 --> 00:00:21,159
<i>FRANCIS: It's Father.
He's gone utterly mad.</i>

11
00:00:21,226 --> 00:00:22,794
You think I'm delusional?

12
00:00:22,828 --> 00:00:25,063
French forces marched
for Calais this morning.

13
00:00:25,131 --> 00:00:27,298
I need the Duke's army to save France.

14
00:00:27,366 --> 00:00:29,500
We stay and finish this or we die trying.

15
00:00:29,568 --> 00:00:31,002
Fire!

16
00:00:37,476 --> 00:00:39,610
(crowd cheering)

17
00:00:53,425 --> 00:00:55,059
MARY: Did you see Francis yet?

18
00:00:55,093 --> 00:00:56,560
Not yet.

19
00:00:56,627 --> 00:00:58,328
It's strange how, after months of waiting,

20
00:00:58,396 --> 00:01:00,530
these last moments are the most agonizing.

21
00:01:00,598 --> 00:01:02,566
What about you? Don't you
want to look for Leith?

22
00:01:02,633 --> 00:01:04,601
He was conscripted so he
wouldn't be punished here.

23
00:01:04,635 --> 00:01:06,837
If he survived, he would never return.

24
00:01:06,871 --> 00:01:08,739
It's better that he doesn't.

25
00:01:08,773 --> 00:01:11,174
Why isn't Bash here to greet his brother?

26
00:01:11,209 --> 00:01:15,445
He's out in the Blood Wood
again hunting for the Darkness.

27
00:01:15,479 --> 00:01:20,116
(sighs) Why Bash feels it's his
duty to end this, I don't know.

28
00:01:20,150 --> 00:01:22,519
I just want him to come home to me.

29
00:01:22,553 --> 00:01:25,922
Take me away from court and our mad king.

30
00:01:25,956 --> 00:01:28,624
MAN: God save Prince Francis!

31
00:01:28,658 --> 00:01:30,693
200 years!

32
00:01:30,728 --> 00:01:33,562
For 200 years the English have occupied

33
00:01:33,597 --> 00:01:36,199
our port city of Calais, but no longer!

34
00:01:36,233 --> 00:01:38,768
(crowd cheers)

35
00:01:38,802 --> 00:01:41,370
Calais is ours once again!

36
00:01:41,404 --> 00:01:43,405
(cheering)

37
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:46,375
And I am proud to say
that I fought alongside

38
00:01:46,409 --> 00:01:49,378
the bravest soldiers in Europe,

39
00:01:49,412 --> 00:01:51,747
And the Duke of Guise, whose men

40
00:01:51,781 --> 00:01:54,816
and bravery helped us achieve victory!

41
00:01:54,851 --> 00:01:56,585
(cheering)

42
00:01:59,956 --> 00:02:01,757
Mention your father, Francis.

43
00:02:01,791 --> 00:02:04,392
Don't let that son of a bitch do it first.

44
00:02:04,426 --> 00:02:07,229
In truth, the real hero of Calais

45
00:02:07,263 --> 00:02:09,231
is the man with the vision...

46
00:02:09,265 --> 00:02:14,402
of a France free and whole!

47
00:02:14,436 --> 00:02:18,339
The man who masterminded this victory!

48
00:02:19,275 --> 00:02:21,976
King Henry Valois!

49
00:02:22,043 --> 00:02:24,279
(crowd cheering)

50
00:02:24,313 --> 00:02:27,649
We have our work cut
out for us with that one.

51
00:02:27,716 --> 00:02:28,949
Get to it.

52
00:02:28,984 --> 00:02:30,818
MAN: King Henry!

53
00:02:30,852 --> 00:02:32,420
Mary.

54
00:02:32,454 --> 00:02:34,288
Francis...

55
00:02:34,355 --> 00:02:37,925
you came back to me. You came back.

56
00:02:37,993 --> 00:02:39,426
God is on our side.

57
00:02:39,460 --> 00:02:43,030
Not only did we reclaim Calais,
but I have news of my own:

58
00:02:43,064 --> 00:02:44,799
my spies in England have been tracking

59
00:02:44,866 --> 00:02:48,102
the queen's slow crawl to the grave.

60
00:02:48,170 --> 00:02:50,704
After countless rumors and endless waiting,

61
00:02:50,738 --> 00:02:52,972
she is dead!

62
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:56,677
The queen of England, Mary Tudor, is dead!

63
00:02:56,744 --> 00:02:58,077
(crowd cheering)

64
00:03:00,114 --> 00:03:02,015
The Tudor queen betrayed
the Catholic Church,

65
00:03:02,049 --> 00:03:06,186
her own faith, by naming
a Protestant to the throne.

66
00:03:06,220 --> 00:03:10,990
But God's will reigns.

67
00:03:11,058 --> 00:03:16,296
We will take the time
to relish our victories,

68
00:03:16,363 --> 00:03:19,332
knowing that one day England will be ours,

69
00:03:19,399 --> 00:03:23,336
crushed and then reborn
under its rightful queen,

70
00:03:23,403 --> 00:03:25,671
Mary Stuart!

71
00:03:25,739 --> 00:03:27,940
(cheering)

72
00:03:30,477 --> 00:03:33,779
(fast tempo acoustic intro playing)

73
00:03:35,114 --> 00:03:39,985
♪ They all need
something to hold on to ♪

74
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:43,155
♪ They all mean well ♪

75
00:03:43,223 --> 00:03:46,191
♪ You could never feel my story ♪

76
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:50,462
♪ It's all you know... oh! ♪

